00:13:08,300 --> 00:13:11,260
♪The tapestry of destiny
is filled with our youth♪

307
00:13:12,660 --> 00:13:20,300
♪Our blissful time together
will lead us to the sea of stars♪

308
00:13:21,020 --> 00:13:30,580
[Chaoyu Yard]

309
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:31,360
Father.

310
00:13:31,670 --> 00:13:32,440
You're back, Si.

311
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:33,750
Zhan.

312
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:36,960
Father,

313
00:13:37,550 --> 00:13:38,670
what are you doing?

314
00:13:39,550 --> 00:13:40,510
Airing out calligraphy and paintings?

315
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:42,440
Zhan said

316
00:13:42,670 --> 00:13:44,240
you wanted to buy a store.

317
00:13:47,360 --> 00:13:47,870
Father,

318
00:13:48,240 --> 00:13:49,840
these are the collections
you've built over the years.

319
00:13:49,960 --> 00:13:51,360
How can you bear to pawn them?

320
00:13:51,910 --> 00:13:52,480
I'll figure

321
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:53,750
something out to buy the store myself.

322
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:56,910
You're an unmarried lady.

323
00:13:57,030 --> 00:13:58,750
What solutions can you possibly have?

324
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:00,200
Father, here's my plan.

325
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:01,390
I can rent

326
00:14:01,390 --> 00:14:02,360
a store first.

327
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:03,630
It won't cost much.

328
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:05,360
Then, I'll use some of the dowry

329
00:14:05,360 --> 00:14:06,510
Mother left me.

330
00:14:06,670 --> 00:14:07,480
That should suffice.

331
00:14:07,790 --> 00:14:09,320
Once the business improves,

332
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:10,630
I'll buy the store.

333
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:12,840
No renting. Just buy it.

334
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:15,030
My daughter wants to do business.

335
00:14:15,150 --> 00:14:16,790
How could her father

336
00:14:16,790 --> 00:14:18,030
not buy her a store?

337
00:14:18,150 --> 00:14:20,870
Keep the dowry.

338
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:24,440
With money in hand,
you can be confident and at ease.

339
00:14:26,270 --> 00:14:28,120
Besides, I only started collecting these

340
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:29,390
when I was young

341
00:14:29,630 --> 00:14:31,000
because the other young gentlemen

342
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:32,200
were buying them too.

343
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:33,870
I've already grown out of them

344
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,670
after all these years.

345
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:37,440
Your brother's pieces

346
00:14:37,510 --> 00:14:38,960
are even more useless.

347
00:14:39,270 --> 00:14:41,360
He was excited for a few days
after buying them,

348
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:43,390
but then he left them in the study

349
00:14:43,390 --> 00:14:44,550
and never looked at them again.

350
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:44,910
See.

351
00:14:44,910 --> 00:14:46,360
They've collected thick dust.

352
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:47,000
Exactly.

353
00:14:47,630 --> 00:14:48,720
Those pieces all seemed precious

354
00:14:48,790 --> 00:14:50,270
before they were bought.

355
00:14:50,600 --> 00:14:51,600
But once you had them,

356
00:14:52,150 --> 00:14:53,120
they were nothing special.

357
00:14:53,630 --> 00:14:54,120
Si,

358
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:55,910
just think of it as a favor for me.

359
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:56,910
You have no idea

360
00:14:56,910 --> 00:14:57,550
how cluttered

361
00:14:57,550 --> 00:14:58,720
my study is.

362
00:14:59,150 --> 00:14:59,720
Zhan.

363
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:01,360
Father.

364
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:04,150
Enough said. Give us a hand.

365
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:06,030
He has butterfingers.

366
00:15:06,150 --> 00:15:07,270
We won't get a good price

367
00:15:07,670 --> 00:15:09,120
if they are damaged.

368
00:15:09,510 --> 00:15:10,150
Father.

369
00:15:11,790 --> 00:15:13,120
Are you really that confident

370
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:15,360
that I can run this store well?

371
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:16,870
Of course.

372
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:18,030
Don't forget

373
00:15:18,270 --> 00:15:21,200
that your maternal grandfather
was the wealthiest man in Lingshui.

374
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:22,790
You're born

375
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:24,320
with a gift

376
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:26,120
for business.

377
00:15:26,510 --> 00:15:26,910
Father.

378
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:29,910
All I do is make merry.

379
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,120
Seems like

380
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:32,240
I inherited that from you.

381
00:15:32,270 --> 00:15:32,960
Get out of here.

382
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:34,550
Didn't I tell you

383
00:15:34,670 --> 00:15:36,200
I picked you up somewhere?

384
00:15:37,550 --> 00:15:38,480
Oh, really?

385
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:40,390
No wonder you're so mean to me.

386
00:15:41,150 --> 00:15:41,910
By the way, Si,

387
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:44,670
don't let your grandmother find out

388
00:15:44,750 --> 00:15:46,720
about your plan.

389
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:48,960
Like most people in Ling'an,

390
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:49,960
she looks down

391
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:52,150
on merchants,

392
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:53,670
let alone allowing

393
00:15:53,750 --> 00:15:55,670
the legitimate daughter of the count
to go into business.

394
00:15:55,910 --> 00:15:56,550
Do you understand?

395
00:15:58,390 --> 00:15:59,240
I understand, Father.

396
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:05,670
Father.

397
00:16:06,120 --> 00:16:07,550
Rue

398
00:16:07,750 --> 00:16:08,910
really works.

399
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:11,120
These books have been stored
for a whole year,

400
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:12,270
and there isn't a single bug bite

401
00:16:12,270 --> 00:16:13,320
found on them.

402
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:14,120
They're intact.

403
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:17,240
My daughter is so clever.

404
00:16:20,270 --> 00:16:21,080
Oh, right, Father,

405
00:16:21,510 --> 00:16:23,480
I rarely hear you talk

406
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:24,750
about the Directorate of Astronomy

407
00:16:25,750 --> 00:16:26,630
or see you catching up

408
00:16:26,630 --> 00:16:28,080
with your former colleagues.

409
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:30,790
After your mother passed,

410
00:16:31,630 --> 00:16:33,000
I lost my passion for the job,

411
00:16:33,960 --> 00:16:36,120
so I resigned.

412
00:16:36,720 --> 00:16:38,080
I've always thought

413
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:39,670
there was something mysterious

414
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:40,910
about observing the stars at night.

415
00:16:41,910 --> 00:16:43,030
You can predict the weather

416
00:16:43,440 --> 00:16:44,600
and foresee fortunes.

417
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:47,320
Studying the universe

418
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:50,080
is indeed fascinating.

419
00:16:51,390 --> 00:16:52,790
But in the Directorate of Astronomy,

420
00:16:53,750 --> 00:16:55,440
it's not just about the universe.

421
00:16:56,750 --> 00:16:58,240
Instead, there are

422
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:00,550
more flatterers

423
00:17:01,270 --> 00:17:03,310
and helpless situations.

424
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:04,200
Father.

425
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:07,030
Do you remember

426
00:17:07,109 --> 00:17:07,720
you used to force me

427
00:17:07,750 --> 00:17:09,270
to practice calligraphy?

428
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:10,200
Look,

429
00:17:10,829 --> 00:17:12,400
I found a copybook.

430
00:17:13,310 --> 00:17:14,640
I remember this copybook.

431
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:16,240
Back then,

432
00:17:16,240 --> 00:17:17,829
every time I bought one,

433
00:17:17,880 --> 00:17:19,440
it would disappear.

434
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:20,960
It was very strange.

435
00:17:22,349 --> 00:17:23,680
I threw them all away.

436
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:24,960
I helped you throw out a few.

437
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:26,349
That explains why your handwriting

438
00:17:26,349 --> 00:17:27,880
looks like a chicken scratch.

439
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:29,350
Don't sell this.

440
00:17:29,350 --> 00:17:30,270
Take it back and keep practicing.

441
00:17:30,550 --> 00:17:31,030
No.

442
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:31,960
I'll sell this one first.

443
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:33,270
Aji, quick!

444
00:17:33,270 --> 00:17:33,790
Sell this copybook first!

445
00:17:33,790 --> 00:17:34,830
Stop right there!

446
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:35,960
Don't sell that one.

447
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:36,920
If you do,

448
00:17:36,920 --> 00:17:38,960
you'll be grounded for a whole month!

449
00:17:38,960 --> 00:17:39,720
Don't sell it.

450
00:17:39,750 --> 00:17:40,790
Stop right there!

451
00:17:47,920 --> 00:17:48,590
My Lady,

452
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:49,880
[Lushengxiang Store]
we still can't find anyone

453
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:51,550
willing to work for our store.

454
00:17:51,680 --> 00:17:52,920
The women of Ling'an City
refused outright

455
00:17:53,030 --> 00:17:54,640
when they heard about doing business.

456
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:56,830
We're about to open the store,

457
00:17:57,070 --> 00:17:58,350
but we're still short on manpower.

458
00:17:58,720 --> 00:17:59,590
What should we do?

459
00:18:01,030 --> 00:18:01,790
Miss Chuchu.

460
00:18:02,640 --> 00:18:03,270
Chuchu.

461
00:18:03,480 --> 00:18:04,550
I heard from Jiang Zhan

462
00:18:04,590 --> 00:18:05,240
that you were looking for help.

463
00:18:06,480 --> 00:18:07,480
I brought someone for you.

464
00:18:07,720 --> 00:18:08,350
[Rou'er]
Nice to meet you, Miss Jiang.

465
00:18:08,830 --> 00:18:10,030
Congratulations

466
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:11,000
on opening your new shop.

467
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:12,110
Nice to meet you, too, Miss Rou'er.

468
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:13,480
Chuchu,

469
00:18:13,680 --> 00:18:14,480
you are

470
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:15,480
a godsend.

471
00:18:15,480 --> 00:18:16,110
Rest assured.

472
00:18:16,160 --> 00:18:17,440
Rou'er is reliable.

473
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:18,960
She's from my hometown.

474
00:18:19,160 --> 00:18:19,680
She once

475
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:20,880
ran a rouge store.

476
00:18:21,750 --> 00:18:22,270
Chief,

477
00:18:22,270 --> 00:18:24,110
you cracked the case
of Marquis of Changxing's Mansion

478
00:18:24,110 --> 00:18:25,240
and gained His Majesty's support.

479
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:26,030
Many officials

480
00:18:26,030 --> 00:18:27,160
are trying to cozy up to us.

481
00:18:27,640 --> 00:18:29,110
Mr. Zhao
from the Secretariat Rear Section

482
00:18:29,110 --> 00:18:29,590
invites you...

483
00:18:29,590 --> 00:18:30,240
I'm too busy to go.

484
00:18:30,830 --> 00:18:31,200
Yes, Chief.

485
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:32,030
Yu.

486
00:18:32,480 --> 00:18:32,830
Jiang.

487
00:18:32,830 --> 00:18:33,480
What a coincidence.

488
00:18:34,310 --> 00:18:35,480
- Looks like you've struck it rich.
- Keep walking.

489
00:18:35,480 --> 00:18:36,510
You bought so many things.

490
00:18:37,110 --> 00:18:38,510
Si is opening a fragrance store

491
00:18:38,510 --> 00:18:39,310
the day after tomorrow.

492
00:18:39,310 --> 00:18:40,270
So I bought her some gifts.

493
00:18:40,350 --> 00:18:41,400
She's opening a fragrance store?

494
00:18:42,160 --> 00:18:43,270
I'm glad I ran into you.

495
00:18:43,720 --> 00:18:44,310
I was just about

496
00:18:44,310 --> 00:18:45,510
to send you the invitation.

497
00:18:45,750 --> 00:18:47,590
You must come by then.

498
00:18:47,640 --> 00:18:48,110
I'm sorry.

499
00:18:48,110 --> 00:18:49,640
Chief is busy on that day.

500
00:18:49,640 --> 00:18:50,240
No, I'm not busy.

501
00:18:51,160 --> 00:18:52,550
I can make time for it.

502
00:18:52,680 --> 00:18:53,510
Of course, I'll be there.

503
00:18:53,550 --> 00:18:54,350
Good to know.

504
00:18:54,680 --> 00:18:55,680
Lushengxiang.
[*Literally "Fragrant Dew"]

505
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:57,160
What a nice name.

506
00:19:07,750 --> 00:19:08,400
Long Dan.

507
00:19:10,680 --> 00:19:11,350
Long Dan.

508
00:19:13,270 --> 00:19:13,880
What's wrong, Chief?

509
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:15,240
Where did you put it?

510
00:19:15,790 --> 00:19:16,550
What?

511
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:18,030
The thing I asked you to bring.

512
00:19:18,030 --> 00:19:18,880
Where did you put it?

513
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:19,590
You didn't ask me to bring anything.

514
00:19:19,590 --> 00:19:20,240
What is it?

515
00:19:20,880 --> 00:19:21,880
Where's my bronze mirror?

516
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:23,200
Where did you put it?

517
00:19:23,240 --> 00:19:24,640
We don't have one.

518
00:19:26,310 --> 00:19:27,550
Borrow one from our neighbor.

519
00:19:27,550 --> 00:19:28,350
Now. Quickly.

520
00:19:28,350 --> 00:19:28,880
I...

521
00:19:54,790 --> 00:19:55,680
Chief.

522
00:19:55,720 --> 00:19:56,750
Bronze mirror.

523
00:19:57,270 --> 00:19:57,960
Here's a bronze mirror.

524
00:20:00,350 --> 00:20:00,920
Slow down.

525
00:20:00,920 --> 00:20:01,640
Here.

526
00:20:11,160 --> 00:20:12,790
Chief, are you going to meet Miss Jiang

527
00:20:13,880 --> 00:20:14,880
in this attire?

528
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:16,400
How do I look?

529
00:20:17,030 --> 00:20:18,240
You're...

530
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:22,880
You're incredibly dashing.

531
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:24,030
You'll definitely amaze

532
00:20:24,030 --> 00:20:25,110
Miss Jiang.

533
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:29,110
Haven't I always been so dashing?

534
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:30,590
Yes. Right.

535
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:33,790
Sound the gong at the auspicious hour

536
00:20:34,680 --> 00:20:36,200
to mark the grand opening,

537
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:39,350
summoning luck and blessings.

538
00:20:39,480 --> 00:20:42,480
Let the mirror reflect your heart,
and conduct business with devotion,

539
00:20:42,550 --> 00:20:45,550
integrity, and discipline.

540
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:52,070
The mellow fragrance

541
00:20:52,110 --> 00:20:53,550
spreads far and wide.

542
00:20:54,510 --> 00:20:55,680
Place the gourd

543
00:20:55,790 --> 00:20:56,880
to welcome fortune.

544
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:58,480
May this new business flourish.

545
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:02,030
Look at those gentlemen there.

546
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:03,110
They're so handsome.

547
00:21:03,110 --> 00:21:05,310
Impressive, Yu.

548
00:21:05,590 --> 00:21:07,920
You look dashing today.

549
00:21:09,350 --> 00:21:11,750
Mr. Zhen, thank you for coming.

550
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:12,440
Thank you.

551
00:21:15,110 --> 00:21:16,750
Mr. Zhen, didn't you say

552
00:21:16,880 --> 00:21:18,920
that civil servants mustn't slack off

553
00:21:19,030 --> 00:21:21,070
even on their off days?

554
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:22,720
I did.

555
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:25,510
But Miss Jiang

556
00:21:25,590 --> 00:21:26,550
personally came

557
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:27,790
to deliver an invitation yesterday.

558
00:21:28,510 --> 00:21:29,750
How could I say no

559
00:21:30,070 --> 00:21:31,000
to such a wonderful occasion?

560
00:21:31,270 --> 00:21:32,070
Thank you so much.

561
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:33,240
Really?

562
00:21:34,240 --> 00:21:34,720
Why?

563
00:21:35,350 --> 00:21:36,720
Did you not receive an invitation

564
00:21:36,720 --> 00:21:37,790
from Miss Jiang, Commandant Yu?

565
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:39,440
Of course, I did.

566
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:40,750
That's why I'm here.

567
00:21:41,920 --> 00:21:43,000
We happened to run into each other

568
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:45,480
on the way before she could deliver it,

569
00:21:45,480 --> 00:21:46,790
saving her the trouble

570
00:21:46,790 --> 00:21:47,880
of making the trip.

571
00:21:48,790 --> 00:21:49,480
I see.

572
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:50,830
What a coincidence.

573
00:21:51,750 --> 00:21:52,070
Chief,

574
00:21:52,070 --> 00:21:53,310
didn't you say
it was Jiang Zhan who invited you...

575
00:21:55,880 --> 00:21:57,440
Miss Si, you may unveil it.

